This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as constituent parsing. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces novel dynamic oracles for training shift-reduce algorithms. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing more accurate parsing models. The use of dynamic oracles also suggests a potential connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper's focus on achieving state-of-the-art results on a benchmark dataset could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
